verbose_text: Newly diagnosed diabetic patients have lower PLP concentrations when compared to non diabetic subjects [XREF_BIBR] Even though a long-term placebo controlled trial of combined folic acid, pyridoxine and B12 supplementation found no differences in the risk of developing type 2 diabetes in women with high risk of CVD, although homocysteine levels were lower in the supplemented group [XREF_BIBR].
